		<title>Hong Kong Stocks Look to End a Recent Correction</title>
		<link>https://www.atfx.com/en/analysis/market-news/hong-kong-stocks-end-recent-correction</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[ATFX]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Sun, 14 Jul 2024 17:26:44 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[Market news & Insights]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Hang Seng]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Recent news]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.atfx.com/?p=37536</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[Hong Kong stocks have been on a correction over the last two months, but that may be ending. HK 50 – Daily Chart  The HK 50 saw a correction after the May breakout of strong downtrend resistance. A rally has now formed, with the price now trading at 18,293, and the index will look to [&#8230;]]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://www.atfx.com/en/markets/hk-share-cfd" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Hong Kong stocks</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> have been on a correction over the last two months, but that may be ending.</span></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-37535" src="https://www.atfx.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/HK-50-–-Daily-Chart.png" alt="HK 50 – Daily Chart" width="976" height="639" srcset="https://www.atfx.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/HK-50-–-Daily-Chart.png 976w, https://www.atfx.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/HK-50-–-Daily-Chart-300x196.png 300w, https://www.atfx.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/HK-50-–-Daily-Chart-768x503.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 976px) 100vw, 976px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-weight: 400; font-size: 10pt;">HK 50 – Daily Chart </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The</span> <a href="https://www.atfx.com/en/markets/indices-trading" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><span style="font-weight: 400;">HK 50</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> saw a correction after the May breakout of strong downtrend resistance. A rally has now formed, with the price now trading at 18,293, and the index will look to push toward the 20,000 level. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Last week&#8217;s softer-than-expected US inflation reading boosted expectations that the Federal Reserve will cut interest rates at its September meeting. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Property stocks were mainly supported, with Sun Hung Kai Properties and other Hong Kong-based developers rallying on the prospect that the rate cut would revive home sales in the region. The Hong Kong dollar&#8217;s peg to the US dollar means the Hong Kong Monetary Authority has to raise or cut the city&#8217;s benchmark interest rate in lockstep with the Fed&#8217;s rate changes. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Bank stock earnings in the United States also hinted at a slowdown in consumer spending and stress among borrowers. That could feed into further rate cuts, and the US stock rallied on Friday. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The Chinese economy&#8217;s growth figures will be released on Monday, which could also boost stocks. The forecast is for 5.1% after 5.3% last month, but there is still potential for a better-than-expected result. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">China&#8217;s ruling party also starts its third plenum meeting this week to discuss the outlook for the economy. That could bring positive news for the market with the potential for further property market reforms or support. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Chinese authorities also suspended short-selling in the stock market last week, which could help stock prices in the coming weeks. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">There will also be little data from the United States in the week ahead. However, a European interest rate decision may affect the dollar.</span></p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
